description: The Karnataka Congress government has withdrawn general consent for the CBI to investigate new cases against public servants, citing bias in the agency. This move aligns with actions taken by other non-BJP states and follows BJP's demand for a probe into a land-allotment case involving CM Siddaramaiah's wife. Ongoing investigations remain unaffected.

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi motivated BJP workers in Haryana to strive hard for the upcoming elections, predicting a third term victory. description: Kyiv endured another night of air raid alerts and drone attacks, leading to explosions across various districts. Residents often take refuge in bomb shelters, with children and the elderly particularly affected. description: Mukti Ranjan Ray, the main suspect in the brutal murder of Mahalakshmi in Bengaluru, reportedly committed suicide in Odisha. He had strangled and dismembered her body after an altercation. Mukti's brother stated that he intended to dispose of the remains later. Police believe he took his own life fearing arrest as they were closing in on him.

description: China and India have made progress in reducing differences and reaching a consensus on disengaging troops from friction points in eastern Ladakh. Shah reiterated that Article 370 will not be restored and emphasized grassroots democracy initiatives.

description: ​"Meg squeezed some onto her finger and applied it to her lips. Kate grimaced. Small clash of styles, maybe? Something we should've been able to laugh about soon after. But it left a little mark. And then the press sensed something was up and tried to turn it into something bigger. Here we go, I thought sorrowfully," Harry wrote.

description: The Supreme Court has emphasised that rigorous bail provisions in statutes like PMLA, UAPA, and NDPS Act should not serve as tools to keep undertrial accused imprisoned for prolonged periods. Granting bail to former Tamil Nadu minister Senthil Balaji after 15 months of incarceration, the court highlighted the necessity of swift trial proceedings.

description: ​Social media users asked why it was terrible for the woman. "A Chinese seething about immigrants in Canada is something..." a user wrote. "Was in Canada a few months ago and can confirm, although the remaining white Canadians are still very nice people, but maybe they're too nice for their own good," another wrote.

description: NCP leader Supriya Sule called on PM Modi to inaugurate Pune Metro's new phase online, pointing out this would be his sixth inauguration of the project. She criticized delays as politically motivated. Local leaders warned they would open the Metro if the government does not act soon.

description: Over 600,000 users, including celebrities like James McAvoy and Tom Brady, shared a false message claiming to prevent Meta from using their images for AI training. Meta clarified that sharing the message does not affect privacy settings. Users can opt out through account settings in line with data protection laws.

description: The Mr. McMahon docuseries on Netflix explores Vince McMahon's influential yet controversial role in WWE. Directed by Chris Smith, it features over 100 hours of interviews with McMahon, his family, and wrestling legends. The series offers a balanced view of his impact on professional wrestling, blending historical context with personal insights.

description: A woman was thrown out of Disney California Adventure Park for attempting to sneak her children in for free by passing them off as under 3 years old. She was arrested for trespassing but later released on a citation. Similar incidents have occurred at other Disney parks in the past.

description: MS Dhoni’s renowned helicopter shot was taught to him by his childhood friend Santosh Lal. They played cricket together in Ranchi and worked for the Railways. While Dhoni achieved global fame, Santosh stayed at the state level. In 2013, despite Dhoni’s efforts for advanced medical treatment, Santosh succumbed to pancreatitis.

description: India has advanced to the 39th spot among 133 global economies in the Global Innovation Index (GII) 2024, an improvement from last year's rank of 40. This progress is driven by India's vibrant start-up ecosystem, knowledge capital, and significant contributions from both public and private research organizations. India continues to lead the lower-middle-income group for the 14th consecutive year.
title: India climbs to 39th rank in the Global Innovation Index 2024

description: President Joe Biden unveiled an $8 billion security aid package for Ukraine, featuring a glide bomb to enhance its strike capabilities against Russia. Russian President Vladimir Putin cautioned about revising Russia's nuclear doctrine in response to such threats.

description: The Sahara Desert is undergoing a rare transformation as heavy rainfall brings unexpected greenery to its arid landscape. Satellite images show vegetation emerging in typically barren regions across Morocco, Algeria, Tunisia, and Libya. This unusual event raises questions about climate change's impact on Africa's rainfall patterns.
title: Nasa shares stunning images of unusual greenery in Sahara Desert following rainfall

description: Star Health has initiated legal proceedings against Telegram and a hacker for leaking sensitive customer information via chatbots. A Tamil Nadu court has temporarily ordered the blocking of these chatbots and websites. Additionally, Star Health sued Cloudflare, alleging its services hosted the leaked data. The next hearing is set for October 25.
title: Star Health hacking: Insurance giant sues Telegram after data leak

description: Lamar Jackson earned the NFL MVP Award for the 2023 season while Patrick Mahomes clinched his third Lombardi Trophy. The article highlights top NFL quarterbacks of 2024 like Jackson, Mahomes, Joe Burrow, Justin Herbert, and Jordan Love. It details their notable achievements and recent performances in the league.

description: Indian chess grandmaster R Praggnanandhaa expressed happiness after winning gold at the 45th Chess Olympiad and meeting Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi. He emphasized the dedication behind this historic achievement for Indian chess. Both men's and women's teams secured gold, marking a significant milestone for India's chess community and inspiring future enthusiasts nationwide.
title: 'Conversation with PM Modi went over an hour': Chess Olympiad gold medallist Praggnanandhaa

description: Former Delhi Deputy CM Manish Sisodia accused PM Narendra Modi and the BJP of "killing democracy" in the Delhi Municipal Corporation. His comments followed an order from Delhi LG VK Saxena to complete the MCD Standing Committee election by 10 pm, even though Mayor Shelly Oberoi had adjourned the House until October 5 due to chaos.

description: Pakistan has advised its citizens to brace for 'transitional pain' following the IMF's approval of a $7 billion relief package with an immediate disbursement of $1 billion. description: The Centre has announced an increase in minimum wage rates through a revision of the Variable Dearness Allowance. This decision will benefit workers across various sectors such as construction and agriculture. The new rates will be effective from October 1, 2024, following the last revision in April 2024. This move aims to help workers cope with rising living costs.

description: Pune Police have brought additional charges against a 17-year-old juvenile involved in a fatal Porsche crash that killed two IT professionals. description: Vice President Jagdeep Dhankhar voiced concerns over the structured rise of religious conversions in India, particularly among tribal communities. He described this trend as a dangerous indication that could reshape the political landscape and urged immediate action to counter these efforts, stressing the importance of preserving cultural and spiritual values.

description: India's cricket team faces uncertainty regarding captaincy if Rohit Sharma is injured during the second Test against Bangladesh, as no vice-captain has been named. description: As BJP distanced itself from MP Kangana Ranaut's remarks on repealed farm laws, ally Chirag Paswan defended her as new to politics. Ranaut apologised, clarifying that her views don't represent the BJP's stance. Congress demanded her expulsion and called for Prime Minister Modi to clarify his position on the issue.

description: Cristiano Ronaldo, one of football’s most decorated players, has won numerous trophies throughout his career. His achievements include five UEFA Champions League titles, three Premier League titles, two La Liga titles, and two Serie A titles. Additionally, he has led Portugal to victory in the UEFA European Championship and the UEFA Nations League.

description: Khatron Ke Khiladi 14's grand finale is scheduled for this weekend, where the winner will be announced. Promos have highlighted finalist Shalin Bhanot's daring stunts. description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has not responded to a US and French proposal for a 21-day ceasefire with Hezbollah in Lebanon, directing the military to continue its operations. IDF chief Herzi Halevi warned of an imminent ground offensive against Hezbollah. The conflict in Gaza is also escalating, despite international calls for restraint and diplomacy.

description: In Bihar, 43 people, including 37 children, drowned and three others went missing during the 'Jivitputrika' festival held on Wednesday. The incidents occurred across 15 districts as women fasted for their children's well-being. CM Nitish Kumar announced an ex gratia payment of ₹4 lakh to the victims' families in Aurangabad.

description: The Congress-led Siddaramaiah government in Karnataka has withdrawn its 'open consent' for the CBI to investigate within the state, citing concerns of misuse and bias. Court-directed CBI investigations will remain unaffected by this withdrawal.

description: Maye Musk addressed the rumours of her son, Elon Musk, dating Georgia Meloni after a viral photo led to public speculation. She clarified that she was seated next to Elon and admired Meloni. Elon Musk also denied the claims. The rumours were fueled by his praise for Meloni at an awards ceremony in New York.

description: Coldplay's India concert ticket demand crashed BookMyShow, sparking a flood of memes and social media buzz. Fans faced long virtual queues trying to secure tickets for the Mumbai shows. The frenzy prompted Coldplay to add a third show in Mumbai, highlighting their immense popularity after a nine-year hiatus.

description: Bangladesh's experienced all-rounder Shakib Al Hasan announced his wish to retire from Test cricket after a final match in Mirpur against South Africa or the upcoming second Test against India. He also revealed that he has already played his last T20 match. Shakib has had a notable career with substantial contributions in both batting and bowling.

description: Arvind Kejriwal, former CM and AAP national convener, stated that a senior BJP leader admitted to wanting to derail the Delhi government by having him arrested. Kejriwal voiced concern over these alleged motives and reassured Delhi's residents that he would continue addressing their issues despite recent setbacks.

description: The BJP rebuked Jharkhand chief minister Hemant Soren for comparing the RSS to rats, stating it comprises 'Hindu lions' restoring Sanatan dharma. They accused Soren of supporting Bangladeshi infiltrators for political gain and disputed his remarks on demographic changes in Jharkhand, particularly in Bhognadih.

description: The Armed Forces (Special Powers) Act has been extended for six months in eight districts of Nagaland and three districts of Arunachal Pradesh. Declared as 'disturbed areas' by the Union Home Ministry, this extension is effective from October 1, 2024. The AFSPA grants armed forces the authority to search, arrest, and open fire if necessary to maintain public order.

description: The Indian cricket team is undecided on its playing XI for the second Test against Bangladesh in Kanpur, starting on Friday. The choice of spinners and pacers will hinge on pitch and weather conditions, with rain expected. A final decision, including possibly adding a third spinner, will be made just before the toss.

description: Robert Vadra, businessman and husband of Congress leader Priyanka Gandhi Vadra, criticised Prime Minister Modi for his 'dalaal, damaad' remark made during a rally in Haryana. Vadra expressed disappointment over the tone used by PM Modi and mentioned that various investigations have not proven any wrongdoing on his part. He believes the people of Haryana desire change.
title: 'Expect much more ... ': Robert Vadra on PM Modi's 'dalaal, damaad' attack

description: President Emmanuel Macron of France has backed the expansion of the United Nations Security Council to include permanent seats for India, Germany, Japan, Brazil, and two African countries. This proposal aims to make the council more inclusive and reflective of contemporary global realities. ​​US President Joe Biden has also reaffirmed his support for India's demand.

description: The BCCI plans to unveil new retention rules for the IPL mega auction, allowing teams to retain up to five players and scrapping the Right to Match option. This aims at balancing team stability with competitive auctions. The specifics of retention costs and overseas player limits are yet to be finalized.

description: Former batsman Ahmed Shehzad has slammed PCB selector Mohammad Yousuf for excluding some domestic performers from Pakistan's Test squad against England. He was particularly upset about Kamran Ghulam's omission and accused the board of favoritism towards Abdullah Shafique. Shehzad also criticized the Champions Cup, calling it a distraction tactic by PCB management.

description: Iwao Hakamata, once a professional boxer, was acquitted after spending nearly half a century on death row for a crime he did not commit. DNA evidence revealed his innocence, leading to his release in 2014. His case has exposed significant flaws in Japan's legal system and sparked debates over its reliance on confessions and use of the death penalty.

description: Hindu Sena has filed a lawsuit in Ajmer seeking to declare the Khwaja Moinuddin Chishti Dargah as a Shiva temple, claiming it was built on an ancient temple site. This move has sparked significant outrage among Muslims. The court has postponed the hearing to October 10 due to jurisdictional issues.
title: Hindu Sena in court to declare Ajmer dargah a temple, sparks outrage

description: Israeli finance minister Bezalel Smotrich has turned down a 21-day ceasefire proposal, stating that the offensive should conclude with Hezbollah's defeat. The US and its allies had suggested the ceasefire to prevent further escalation. Israeli airstrikes have hit multiple Hezbollah targets in Lebanon, as concerns about a full-scale war grow.
title: Israel rejects ceasefire plans, says goal to 'crush' Hezbollah in Lebanon

description: The IMF's executive board has approved a $7 billion loan for Pakistan to aid its struggling economy. Disbursed over 37 months, the first tranche of $1 billion is available immediately. Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif expressed gratitude for the support, which follows reforms and increased tax measures required by the IMF.
title: IMF approves $7 billion loan for cash-starved Pakistan

description: India looks to secure a clean sweep against Bangladesh in the second Test starting Friday. Key players like Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma need to perform well, while Rishabh Pant shows promise. The Green Park pitch favors spinners, and weather conditions could be challenging. Bangladesh may adjust their lineup after their struggles in the first Test.
title: Ind vs Ban, 2nd Test: India poised to maintain upper hand against Bangladesh

description: Virat Kohli's recent batting issues have become a focal point before the second Test against Bangladesh. In the first Test, he managed only 6 and 17 runs. During practice sessions, he struggled notably against Jasprit Bumrah and India's spinners. All eyes are on Kohli to see if he can regain his form in the upcoming match.
title: Kohli's struggles continue, Bumrah dominates star batter at nets in Kanpur

description: In Navi Mumbai, police arrested seven Bangladeshi women for illegal residency. A raid at Krave village led to their apprehension from two rooms where they lived without proper documentation. Employed as domestic helps, they now face charges under the Passport (Entry into India) Act, 1950, and the Foreigners Act.
title: 7 Bangladeshi women held for illegal stay in Navi Mumbai

description: Isha Ambani and Parita Parekh have secured their spots as the youngest women in the first 2024 Hurun India Under35s list. This list features seven notable women entrepreneurs including Aneri Patel, Aneesha Tiwari, Anjali Merchant, Saloni Anand, and Ghazal Alagh.
title: Isha, Akash Ambani in Hurun India Under 35s entrepreneurs list

description: Former Indian cricketer Yuvraj Singh recounted his historic '6 sixes in an over' against Stuart Broad during the 2007 T20 World Cup. He revealed that a heated exchange with Andrew Flintoff spurred his performance. On a podcast, Yuvraj humorously was told about the 96 million views on the video of his 6 sixes on ICC's YouTube channel.
title: 96 million views! Yuvraj advised to send ICC an invoice

description: As per the latest hearing at the Bombay High Court, the CBFC has decided to give certification to the Kangana Ranaut starrer only if they make the suggested cuts. The production house has asked for time to decide if they want to make those cuts. The next hearing will take place on September 30.
title: Kangana's 'Emergency' can be released if cuts are made: CBFC to court

description: A Mumbai magistrate's court has convicted MP Sanjay Raut in a defamation case filed by Professor Medha Kirit Somaiya, sentencing him to 15 days' simple imprisonment and a Rs 25,000 fine. The case involved defamatory statements made by Raut against Medha, which were published and circulated widely.
title: Sanjay Raut convicted in defamation case filed BJP leader Kirit Somaiya's wife

description: Artem Chigvintsev, recently absolved of domestic violence charges, has finally addressed the situation. He expressed relief over the dropped charges and stressed his focus on co-parenting his son Matteo with estranged wife Nikki Garcia. The couple is currently negotiating a shared custody arrangement to ensure their son's well-being.
title: Artem Chigvintsev speaks out following domestic violence arrest

description: Popular YouTuber Harsha Sai is facing rape allegations after a Mumbai actress filed a complaint with Narsingi police in Hyderabad. She accuses him of blackmailing her with compromising photos and videos and making false promises of marriage. The investigation is ongoing, but no arrest has been made so far.
title: YouTuber Harsha Sai with 15mn followers accused of shooting naked videos

description: Yuvraj Singh shared a personal story from the 2007/08 Border-Gavaskar series on a podcast, revealing he was dating an actress who followed him to Canberra despite his request for space. This led to a humorous incident where he had to wear her pink slip-ons, much to the amusement of his teammates.
title: Yuvraj reveals 'untold' story: 'Had to wear girlfriend's pink slip-ons...'

description: A recent poll suggests Kamala Harris's gender is a larger hurdle in the upcoming US presidential elections than it was for Hillary Clinton in 2016. Conversely, Donald Trump's gender may work to his advantage. The shift is mainly driven by Democrats, while Republicans' views have shown little change.
title: It's 2024 & gender still bigger ‘hurdle' for Harris than Hillary, polls show

description: The Karnataka Lokayukta's Mysuru office is waiting for directions on the Muda case, involving illegal land acquisition. Activist Krishna has accused former Chief Minister Siddaramaiah and others of misusing their official positions to acquire and exchange land in Mysuru. A special judge has instructed that Krishna's petition be registered as a private complaint.
title: Siddaramaiah row: Yediyurappa’s resignation in 2011 also came after a Lokayukta probe

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi wished former PM Dr. Manmohan Singh a happy 92nd birthday, expressing hopes for his long and healthy life. Congress leaders highlighted Singh's significant contributions to economic reforms and public welfare policies. Rahul Gandhi and Mallikarjun Kharge praised his humility, wisdom, and selfless service to the nation.
title: PM Modi wishes predecessor Manmohan Singh on his 92nd birthday

description: Flipkart's Big Billion Days sale is now live for Plus and VIP members, featuring the Apple iPhone 15 at an effective price of Rs 49,999 after bank and exchange offers.
title: iPhone 15 available at Rs 49,999 in Flipkart sale; how the deal works

description: Donald Trump’s election fundraising campaign has provided $15 million to Launchpad Strategies, yet the purpose remains unclear. Over nine years, $876 million has flowed through Trump’s campaigns to six companies, including Launchpad Strategies. Despite meeting disclosure requirements, the identities of strategists and ultimate fund recipients are unknown, raising transparency issues.
title: Where are donations for Trump’s campaign going? It’s this mystery firm

description: The Supreme Court has granted bail to former Tamil Nadu minister V Senthil Balaji, arrested by the Enforcement Directorate last year for money laundering. Strict conditions were imposed while granting bail. The special court in Chennai has been directed to conclude the case within three months, with daily hearings as per guidelines issued by the top court.
title: SC grants bail to former TN minister Senthil Balaji in money laundering case

description: Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma will look to regain form as India face Bangladesh in the second Test of their series in Kanpur. After underwhelming performances in the first Test, both the players are keen to contribute significantly. A 2-0 series win would bolster India's position atop the World Test Championship leaderboard.
title: Watch: Virat smashes big & long as India hit the nets in Kanpur

description: YSRCP president YS Jagan Mohan Reddy has urged people across the state to offer poojas in temples on Saturday to restore the sanctity of Tirumala. He accused CM N Chandrababu Naidu of spreading false claims about the adulteration of Tirumala's sacred laddu prasadam with animal fat, calling for public participation to counter this misinformation.
title: Tirupati laddu row: Jagan Reddy gives 'pooja' call to cleanse 'sin' committed by Naidu

description: The article delivers daily numerology predictions tailored to individuals based on their birth dates. It guides readers on how to handle the day's challenges and opportunities by focusing on leadership qualities, emotional connections, creative pursuits, work discipline, adaptability to change, nurturing relationships, spiritual growth, perseverance in goals and teamwork dynamics.
title: Numerology predictions today: Read your personalised forecast

description: Kanpur's Kuldeep Yadav is gearing up for the second Test against Bangladesh at Green Park. Despite having an impressive record, he often serves as India's backup spinner. Embracing this uncertainty, Kuldeep focuses on self-improvement and seizing opportunities when they arise. His dedication and adaptability have kept him in contention for a spot in the playing XI.
title: Will Kanpur Test be the best chance to play Kuldeep Yadav?

description: YouTuber Ranveer Allahbadia's channels were hacked, renamed "Tesla," and their videos deleted. Hackers used an AI-generated Elon Musk avatar in a livestream to push a cryptocurrency scam, urging viewers to invest Bitcoin or Ethereum. YouTube has removed the channels for policy violations. Allahbadia has not released an official statement yet.
title: Ranveer Allahbadia’s YouTube videos deleted: Read what the message said

description: Donald Trump has urged Apple to aid the FBI in decrypting phones linked to assassination plots against him. The FBI is struggling to access certain apps and devices related to the investigation. Trump also criticized President Biden for not addressing threats from Iran, suggesting a strong retaliatory stance if he were president.
title: Trump urges Apple to decrypt phones of accused assassins, aid FBI probe

description: Virat Kohli's transformation from an emerging cricketer to a global star started with the 2008 U-19 World Cup. His senior India debut followed in August 2008 and he hasn't looked back since, breaking and creating numerous records. A nostalgic video of Kohli’s early days shows his friends teasing him post an interview.
title: 'Bada aadmi ban gaya!' How 'unknown' Virat's interview was celebrated

description: Virat Kohli and James Anderson are renowned cricketers who have faced each other multiple times. Initially, Anderson dominated by dismissing Kohli four times in 2012. However, Kohli improved significantly over the years. Their rivalry evolved into mutual respect, with Kohli revealing he used to imitate Anderson's bowling action as a young player.
title: When Kohli revealed that he used to copy Anderson's bowling action

description: A seven-year-old boy in Aligarh was allegedly beaten and subjected to cruelty by his teacher for forgetting his school bag. His family filed a police complaint after he recounted the incident. The school's principal denied these allegations, asserting that CCTV footage would disprove them.
title: 7-yr-old boy stripped, beaten, given electric shocks by teacher for forgetting bag

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi praised India's young chess players for their historic achievements at the 45th Chess Olympiad in Budapest. Both men's and women's teams clinched their maiden gold medals by defeating Slovenia and Azerbaijan respectively. Modi interacted with the champions, who presented him with a chessboard, followed by a quick game between Praggnanandhaa and Erigaisi.
title: Watch: PM Modi enjoys chess showdown between Praggnanandhaa and Erigaisi

description: Mira Murati has resigned as OpenAI's chief technology officer to focus on personal exploration. She joined the company in 2017 and briefly served as interim CEO.
title: OpenAI’s CTO Mira Murati resigns: Read what CEO Sam Altman said

description: The Andhra Pradesh BJP has called on YSRCP chief Jagan Mohan Reddy to declare his faith ahead of his visit to the Tirumala temple. This comes amid allegations that 'prasadam' was adulterated during his tenure. The controversy highlights concerns over the quality and sanctity of temple offerings, prompting calls for greater transparency. TTD utilises about 10,000 kg of ghee every day for the laddu 'prasadam.'
title: 'Declare your faith': BJP to Jagan Reddy ahead of his Tirumala visit

description: Kanpur's Kuldeep Yadav is gearing up for the second Test against Bangladesh at Green Park. Despite having an impressive record, he often serves as India's backup spinner. Embracing this uncertainty, Kuldeep focuses on self-improvement and seizing opportunities when they arise. His dedication and adaptability have kept him in contention for a spot in the playing XI.
title: Will Kanpur Test be the best chance to play Kuldeep Yadav?

description: The UP government has invoked Section 56 of the Food Safety and Standards Act, 2006, to address food contamination issues. Eateries must prominently display proprietor and manager details. Joint teams from the Food Safety and Drug Administration, police, and local administration will enforce this order. This move follows a Supreme Court ruling on similar notifications for Kanwar Yatra routes.
title: UP doubles down on mandatory display of eatery owners’ names
BJP MP Kangana takes back her farm law remarks

description: India's foodgrain production for the 2023-24 crop year is estimated to reach a record 332 million tonnes, surpassing last year's nearly 330 million tonnes despite below-normal monsoon rainfall. The agriculture ministry credits improved irrigation infrastructure and digital techniques for yield estimation, ensuring transparency and robustness in data collection.
title: Foodgrain output set to hit record 332 MT

description: At the 79th United Nations General Assembly, Google CEO Sundar Pichai highlighted technology's role in expanding opportunities globally. Sharing personal experiences from his childhood in Chennai, he illustrated how advancements like rotary phones and computers improved lives. Pichai emphasized AI's potential to drive progress similarly to the internet and mobile devices.
title: Sundar Pichai recalls how technology improved his life: 'Growing up in Chennai…'

description: The BAPS Shri Swaminarayan Mandir in Sacramento, California was vandalized with anti-Hindu messages, echoing a recent incident in New York. The Hindu American Foundation and local officials condemned the act, noting an increase in anti-Hindu hate crimes. Authorities are urged to promote safety and respect for all faiths within the community.
title: 'Hindus go back': BAPS temple vandalised in US; 2nd incident in month

description: Former India and CSK captain Mahendra Singh Dhoni has returned from a US vacation amid speculation about his IPL future. The BCCI has yet to announce retention rules, leading to uncertainty about whether CSK can retain him or if he will enter the auction pool. The auction is likely in November.
title: Dhoni back from vacation, IPL retention clarity coming soon

description: Israel has alerted its troops for a potential entry into Lebanon after Hezbollah targeted Tel Aviv with missiles. The US and France are advocating for a 21-day ceasefire to reduce escalating tensions. Lebanese Prime Minister Najib Mikati has appealed to the UN Security Council for an immediate ceasefire, citing Israeli violations of Lebanon's sovereignty.
title: 'Prepare for entry': Israeli forces brace for possible ground ops in Lebanon
Ritika Maloo arrested by CID in midnight swoop after late night hearing

description: Sebi will address the retail speculation in futures and options trading during its board meeting on September 30 while considering stricter rules and margining systems. Additionally, the board might approve a new hybrid investment product for wealthy investors and specific regulations for passive-only fund houses, following extensive feedback on proposed changes.
title: Sebi set to tighten F&O rules to rein in speculative trading

description: Elections in Jammu and Kashmir are under international observation for the first time, with diplomats from 16 countries commending the democratic process. With a turnout exceeding 57% in Phase 2, these elections are considered historic. Observers from the US and Singapore noted similarities to their own countries' elections.
title: Very healthy, very democratic: Foreign observers on J&K polls

description: Jheel Mehta, who played Sonu in Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah, reflects on her time on the show. She describes her relationship with Dilip Joshi, reveals top earners, and highlights script improvisations. Jheel fondly remembers birthday celebrations on set and clarifies that a child marriage storyline was actually a dream sequence.
title: Taarak Mehta's Sonu aka Jheel Mehta on her bond with Dilip Joshi

description: Four Indian full-time MBA programmes feature in the top 100 of QS’s Global Rankings for 2025, with IIM Bangalore leading at 53rd place. Despite drops in rankings, three Indian institutions are among the global top 50 for employability. India leads Asia's rankings with a total of 14 MBA programmes listed.
title: 4 Indian MBA courses in QS’s global Top 100, IIM-B leads nationally

description: Russian President Vladimir Putin updated the country's nuclear doctrine, warning that any conventional attack on Russia by a non-nuclear state, if backed by a nuclear power, will be seen as a joint attack. Ukrainian officials called this nuclear blackmail. The Biden administration has not authorized Kyiv to strike inside Russia.
title: Putin issues nuclear warnings to West, Ukraine calls it 'blackmail'

description: Yogeshwar Dutt criticized Vinesh Phogat for her disqualification at the Paris Games, claiming she cost India an Olympic medal. Now a BJP politician, Dutt stated that Vinesh should have apologized to the country instead of blaming others and portraying a wrong image. Vinesh has since joined Congress and is contesting the Haryana Assembly Elections.
title: 'Vinesh Phogat ne ek Olympic medal ka nuksaan karvaya'
Zaggle acquires 26% stake in Mobileware to boost its digital payment capabilities

description: The Greater Chennai Corporation announced the transfer of S B Madhavi, the city's only woman dafadar assigned to escort Mayor R Priya, citing administrative reasons. The corporation clarified that the memo focused on her rule violations and tardiness rather than personal choices or allegations of human rights violations raised by Madhavi in response to an earlier memo.
title: Lipstick row: Chennai's only woman dafadar transferred for 'not carrying out duties'

description: Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah is facing a Lokayukta investigation ordered by a special court over claims of misusing his position to acquire 14 plots for his wife in Mysuru. This follows the Karnataka high court's dismissal of Siddaramaiah's challenge against the governor's sanction for an inquiry into these allegations.
title: K'taka special court orders Lokayukta probe against CM, wife in land case

description: The Himachal Pradesh government has issued a notice requiring restaurants, fast food outlets, and roadside vendors to display ownership details for better accountability in food safety. Following Uttar Pradesh's lead, this measure aims to enhance transparency and hygiene standards. Authorities will now be able to efficiently track food business operators, ensuring compliance with regulations.
title: After UP, Himachal cites hygiene to order eatery owners to display names
'Hard to believe': HC questions police claim of Badlapur encounter
Bike loan company Manba Finance's 151 crore IPO subscribed 224 times
Woman booked for 'shun Hindus' call

description: Hurricane Helene intensifies as it nears Florida, causing destruction in Mexico and leading to evacuations across the Southeast. President Joe Biden declares a state of emergency in Florida. The storm is projected to maintain its strength with winds over 110 mph, expected to make landfall in Florida's Big Bend region.
title: Hurricane Helene prompts mass evacuations in Florida as it nears landfall

description: Mumbai received over 200mm of rain in five hours on Wednesday evening, resulting in four deaths and widespread disruptions including waterlogging, traffic jams, and train delays. The BMC and TMC declared holidays for schools and colleges. A red alert was issued for Mumbai, Thane, and Raigad until Thursday morning. Several flights were diverted due to adverse weather.
title: 200mm rain in 5 hours swamps Mumbai, results in 4 deaths

description: CBI, investigating the rape and murder of an intern at RG Kar Medical College, alleged false records were created at Tala police station. Custodial interrogation revealed altered documents. Lawyers demanded evidence instead of allegations. CBI submitted a sealed report and sought judicial custody of the accused till Sept 30.
title: Kolkata horror: RG Kar evidence 'falsified' at Tala police station, CBI claims in court

description: Celebrities and enterprises are increasingly interested in Swiggy's pre-IPO shares. Notable investors like cricketers Rahul Dravid and Zaheer Khan, tennis star Rohan Bopanna, filmmaker Karan Johar, and actor Ashish Chowdhry have acquired shares. This trend highlights a broader move by high-net-worth individuals to diversify their portfolios with high-growth tech startups.
title: Dravid, Karan & others who have invested in Swiggy’s pre-IPO shares
